# Admin UI/UX rulebook (mandatory — read before any UI change)

Read [`docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`](../../docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md) once. This file is **always applied** in Cursor. Complete the pre-ship checklist (§10) before marking UI work done.

Target: **14" laptop (~1366×768)**. Feel like Linear / Stripe / Ramp — dense, alive, single-viewport.

---

## 1. Foundations

- **Styling**: shadcn semantic tokens + `@/components/ui/*`.
- **Product layout**: `@/components/app/*` (`AppPage`, `AppListCard`, `AppModalFooter`, …).
- **Polaris**: information architecture only. Never for colors or typography.
- **Cards**: `rounded-xl border-border shadow-sm`.
- **Tables**: `TABLE_HEAD_CLASS` on every `TableHead`.

---

## 2. Density — fits one viewport

- Inputs / selects / triggers: **`h-9`**. Never `h-10`/`h-11`.
- Card padding: **`p-4`**. Modal body: **`px-5 py-4`**, **`space-y-3`**.
- Dialog width: **`w-[min(1200px,96vw)]`**.

**Vertical budget (footer-first modals — see §7):**
Footer ≈ 72px + 14" usable ≈ 720px ⇒ body must fit in **≈ 648px**. **Inner scroll in a modal = failure.**

---

## 3. Layout

- Pack identity fields on **one row** (avatar + name + phone + civil id + employee id + driver id).
- Side-by-side cards: **`lg:items-stretch`** + **`h-full`** — no half-empty card.
- Documents / assets: **`lg:grid-cols-4`** on desktop.
- Helper text: **`text-[10px]`** inline; hide when redundant.

---

## 4. Iconography

- Lucide icon on every chip, toggle, and semantic field label.
- Section headers: **`SectionHeading`** with tinted icon chip (Identity=primary, Assignment=violet, Operations=amber, Documents=emerald).

---

## 5. Color — semantic, for STATE

- **Selected / on**: `border-primary/30 bg-primary/10 text-primary`.
- **Active status / uploaded doc**: `border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700`.
- **Required**: red `*` via `text-destructive`.
- **Avatar**: deterministic tint from name — never flat grey.
- **Driver ID badge**: `bg-primary/10 text-primary border-primary/20`.
- Grey-on-grey everywhere = dead UI. Selected must be visually obvious.

---

## 6. Navigation — view page + add/edit modal

| Action | Pattern |
|--------|---------|
| **View / detail** (history, GPS, earnings, tabs) | Full page `/resource/[id]`. **List row click → detail page.** |
| **Add** | Modal on list via `?add=1` |
| **Edit** | Modal only — from detail page **Edit** button or `?edit=1` on detail URL. **Never from row click.** |

- `/resource/new` → redirect to list `?add=1`.
- **Do NOT** redirect `/resource/[id]` to the list.

List row: show subtle **"View details"** link under the name.

---

## 7. Footer-first modals (mandatory)

**Do not waste a top header band** for title/subtitle/close. Reclaim ~56px for content.

- **No top header** in modals. Content starts immediately (`pt-4`).
- **`showCloseButton={false}`** on `DialogContent`.
- Use **`AppModalFooter`** (`@/components/app/app-modal-footer`):
  - **Left stack**: Close button (icon + label) → **title** → **subtitle** (one line).
  - **Right**: Cancel + primary action.
- Title/subtitle use `DialogTitle` / `DialogDescription` for a11y.

Apply this pattern to **all new modals** and when refactoring existing ones.

---

## 8. No chrome inside modals

- No progress steppers, completion %, scroll-spy.
- Footer meta (e.g. draft saved) only when meaningful.

---

## 9. Reference images

Match density, column count, and architecture from user-provided screenshots. Ask before diverging.

---

## 10. Pre-ship checklist

- [ ] One viewport on 14" laptop — no inner scroll
- [ ] Footer-first modal (`AppModalFooter`, no top header)
- [ ] `h-9` inputs, `p-4` cards, semantic color on selected states
- [ ] Section icon chips + tinted avatar + primary Driver ID badge
- [ ] Row click → detail page; edit → modal only
- [ ] Add via `?add=1` modal on list
